subtopics.fact:
For any election before September 1, 2013, a person may provide on of the following:

* A driver's license issued by any state (even if expired);
* ID card issued by the New Hampshire DMV;
* U.S. Armed Services ID card;
* U.S. Passport (even if expired);
* Valid photo ID card issued by either the federal government or state, county or municipal government;
* Valid student ID card;
* Other photo ID deemed legitimate by the supervisors of the checklist, the moderator, or the clerk; or
* Verification of identity by a supervisor of the checklist, the moderator or the clerk
